<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, this species has so far only been recorded from Little Taipa Hill during March-April 1999 and ranges 8-11 mm in total length and 2-3 mm in maximum width. Adults appear to be active in daytime only during the early spring and have been observed mainly feeding on flowers of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and occasionally also of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Oleaceae" genus="Ligustrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ligustrum sinense" order="Oleales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ligustrum sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chou, W-I" journalOrPublisher="Owl Publishing House, Taipei" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B21" refString="Chou, W-I, 2004. The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae. Owl Publishing House, Taipei" title="The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae." year="2004">Chou (2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chou, W-I" journalOrPublisher="Owl Publishing House, Taipei" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B22" refString="Chou, W-I, 2008. The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae (second edition). Owl Publishing House, Taipei" title="The Atlas of Taiwanese Cerambycidae (second edition)." year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
) reported that adults visit flowers and leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1913" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Aceraceae" genus="Acer" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acer cinnamomifolium" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cinnamomifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Acer cinnamomifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Mating pairs and individuals near exit holes have also been found repeatedly on dead trunks of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Zanthoxylum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Zanthoxylum avicennae" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="avicennae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Zanthoxylum avicennae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, indicating that this is possibly one of the host plants for larval development (RP pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
